cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the Internet of Things (IoT) which is a network of connected devices and applications. It also talks about the role of cloud computing in IoT networks deployment. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses resource management in cloud-based IoT environment which involves distributed and parallel computing. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper talks about data analysis process in IoT networks which involves algorithms for converting data into useful information. 
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the challenges and issues of resource allocation in Cloud-based IoT environment which involves software engineering principles for efficient resource utilization and load balancing. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper talks about improving system performance by reducing operational cost and energy consumption which involves control systems principles.
